sec.p:
To minimize the bias of ESMs in projecting the warming level by the end of the 21st century, we assume that the simulated global warming during 2011–20 above pre-industrial levels aligns with the observation of 1.09°C reported by IPCC AR6. Essentially, this is equivalent to discussing the remaining space of future GMST rise on the basis of the current GMST rise of 1.09°C. Therefore, the projected warming level in this study is calculated by adding simulated GMST changes (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
